rComments: Literally one of those Prof's who'd try and make your life easy :) Midterms and exams based on memorization of class lectures.
AMAZING GUY!! Go to this office hours and he will give u hints of whats coming on the test!!
He's very passionate about what he teaches. Gave us a list of 40 questions and said 8 of them will show up on the exam. And he kept his word!
Boring class, but nice proff

Must go to class. Must make your notes. REALLY easy class..but at first midterm everyones marks dropped 20%..its like he jipped us all (he mentioned he has to write a letter to dean if class avg, is high) but if you get lucky its a SUPER easy bird course so it depends. i would take it again. then you can take other relig upper yr birds.
Great Prof! Learnt a lot and definitely a mark booster! Highly Recommended!
by far the easiest course at utm his teaching styles are different but read the assigned readings and lecture notes before class and you'll be fine
I do not recommend any first year taking his courses
Godd Professor BUT MUST READ NOTES! Not too much work but tests difficult if notes not studied carefully.

Most boring class I have ever attended. All his notes are hand-written by him, and most are very illegible. Although going to every class, reading every note and studying very hard, only got a 50% on the first exam. More than half the class failed. DO NOT TAKE THIS CLASS!!!!!!

His mono tone doesn't help ppl keep awake... unforturnatly, his is a very nice guy but if you don't like religion A LOT, you will most likely end up hating the class. sometims it's kind of hard to make out what he is saying
old and sometimes confusing. you think you may know the material but come testing time he wants way too much information
He's a very knowledgeable prof.  Must read textbook since tests are mostly essays.  Level of material too difficult for 100
A really good teacher. Very helpful
study questoins dont help at all, he marks according to the best paper. Insensitve. Not a mark booster at all. He should retire.
No Comments

What a waste. Bring you IPOD to this class, u'll need it. This is the most boring class i'v had in University. ITs a waste of money and time. You learn nothing. This is also not an easy class u won't feel like studying. Avoid

Pitifully bad prof. lectures terribly boring, test expectations ridiculous, you must write down EXACTLY what you read from a very technical, long text package, be prepared to memorize word for word. visitation report a huge mark booster.
Very EASY!!

I just thought he made the course more confusing.  Last time I took world religion it was clear as day.  With HIS course I was confused as hell.  What is "Cosmogany" anyways?  It's been 6 years.  I passed the course and I still don't know.
He makes the course super easy! Definitely a mark booster.

His lectures are extremely boring.  He is a tough marker and take this course only if you are good at writing elaborate answers. This course can boost your GPA UP or DOWN. However, he is a very helpful and there is a LOT of bell curving. You don't even have to attend the lectures and he gives you exam questions before hand to prepare for the finals
Good professor, very helpful but is a hard with explaining materials.  Tests were often brutal but gives a lot of breaks with marking, etc.  Nice professor and workload was average.

he doesnt get along with technology well, but definatly knows what he's talking about ^_^(especially on hindu faith). it's best if you go to his office hours and get help (even just once to talk to him), you usually get a better grasp on things and on how he wants things done.
i will never understand how a prof can take basic material and make it look like the hardest concepts in the world on a test

He is very precise, coures material is a little confusing. He covers it well though, go over ideas many times. Tests are very hard, but there is a lot of bellcurving in this course. Cares about students and has a lot of patience to cover material over if students are confused.
he is very confusing!!!! His tests are also difficult!
BY far the easiest teacher and course in UTM. Take it if you can. RLG 100

Prof Miller, whom I have had the pleasuring of being in his class last year, is a wonderful man. Not only he is there when you need help but he makes sure that you understand a topic before he moves on. Way to go sir!
Lectures are good if you listen..He actually repeats the important stuff a few times.
